- Pass criteria: [for example p95 below X ms]

## 5.3 Security Test Plan

- Authentication and authorization coverage
- Input validation and injection-risk checks
- Sensitive-information exposure checks
- File upload / download / execution-path checks when applicable

## 6. Regression Strategy

- Which paths must keep regression coverage
- What kind of test must be added after a bug fix
- Which changes require a full regression pass

## 7. Execution Guidance

- Start with the smallest high-priority requirement and write the failing test first
- Prioritize paths with high rework risk, complex state transitions, or many edge cases
- If the test framework is not selected yet, write the test idea and assertions first, then choose tools later
- Do not implement first and “add a few tests later”; the tests should drive the design and implementation boundary

## 8. Definition of Completion

- Every high-priority requirement has at least one automated verification path
- Critical failure scenarios are covered
- Bug fixes include regression tests
- Test commands can be run repeatedly with stable results
- White-box, performance, and security requirements relevant to the current version are either satisfied or explicitly deferred with justification
